{
  "name": "Multi-Platform Social Publisher",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Multi-Platform Social Publisher\n\nWhen a blog post is published, this workflow:\n1. Generates platform-tailored copy with an LLM (Facebook, Instagram, X thread, LinkedIn).\n2. Enforces per-platform character limits, appends UTM tags, and attaches hashtags.\n3. Sends every variant to a human for ONE approval via Slack.\n4. Pauses on a Wait node until the approver clicks Approve or Reject (resume-on-webhook).\n5. On approval, fans out to each platform API with retries and per-branch error isolation.\n6. Collects post IDs, appends them to a tracking sheet, and reports the result.\n\nEntry: POST /blog-published  ->  Response: { status, results }",
        "height": 320,
        "width": 460,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "node-0001",
      "name": "Sticky Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-520, -200]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Human Approval Gate\n\nThe **Await Approval** node is a Wait node configured with `resume: webhook`. The run pauses indefinitely and exposes `$execution.resumeUrl`.\n\nThe **Post Approval Request** node sends that URL to Slack with Approve / Reject buttons (Block Kit). The approver's click POSTs `{ decision, edited? }` back to the resume URL, which wakes the exact paused execution.\n\nNothing is published before this gate. A reject path notifies Slack and aborts cleanly.",
        "height": 320,
        "width": 420,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "node-0002",
      "name": "Sticky Approval",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [820, -200]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Per-Platform API Notes\n\n- **Facebook**: POST /{PAGE_ID}/feed with message + link. Page access token via Facebook Graph credential.\n- **Instagram**: two-step. Create media container (POST /{IG_ID}/media), then publish (POST /{IG_ID}/media_publish) with the returned creation_id.\n- **X / Twitter**: thread posted tweet-by-tweet in a Loop, chaining `reply.in_reply_to_tweet_id` to the previous id.\n- **LinkedIn**: POST /v2/ugcPosts as an article share.\n\nEvery API node uses retryOnFail (3 tries, 2s) and continueErrorOutput so one failing platform never blocks the others.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 440,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "node-0003",
      "name": "Sticky Platforms",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [2480, -260]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Setup & Credentials\n\nCredentials (n8n Credential store):\n- facebookGraphApi (FB Page + IG publish)\n- twitterOAuth2Api (X v2)\n- linkedInOAuth2Api\n- httpHeaderAuth (Slack bot token, tracking sheet)\n- OpenAI key on the LLM node\n\nEnv vars:\nFB_PAGE_ID, IG_USER_ID, LINKEDIN_AUTHOR_URN, SLACK_CHANNEL_ID, TRACKING_SHEET_WEBHOOK, OPENAI_MODEL\n\nSee README for the full table and import steps.",
        "height": 340,
        "width": 420,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "node-0004",
      "name": "Sticky Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-520, 180]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
